.TH "tracing_snapshot_cond_enable" 9 "tracing_snapshot_cond_enable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tracing_snapshot_cond_enable \- enable conditional snapshot for an instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tracing_snapshot_cond_enable
.BI "(struct trace_array *tr "  ","
.BI "void *cond_data "  ","
.BI "cond_update_fn_t update "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tr" 12
The tracing instance
.IP "cond_data" 12
User data to associate with the snapshot
.IP "update" 12
Implementation of the cond_snapshot update function
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check whether the conditional snapshot for the given instance has
already been enabled, or if the current tracer is already using a
snapshot; if so, return -EBUSY, else create a cond_snapshot and
save the cond_data and update function inside.

Returns 0 if successful, error otherwise.
